  - name: noncompete_included
    type: boolean
    description: >-
      Whether the non-competition covenant is included. New Jersey has no general
      non-compete statute for the ordinary workforce; a non-compete is
      enforceable only to the extent it satisfies the three-part Solari/Whitmyer
      reasonableness test and is tied to a legitimate interest rather than
      ordinary competition. This template recites the legitimate-interest basis
      and sizes the restraint to the employer's actual footprint.
    display_label: Non-Competition Included
    default: false
    section: Non-Competition
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Conservative default. The non-compete is the most closely scrutinized
      covenant under the Solari/Whitmyer test; a customer non-solicit backstopped
      by the New Jersey Trade Secrets Act often protects the employer as well.
      Include only after confirming an identified legitimate interest
